            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="16"><Run Text="You can drop files "/><Run Text="from"/><Run Text=" your desktop, file explorer, etc, into the notepad list (on the left). You can also drop NotepadItems inside the notepad list on"/><Run Text="to your desktop or file explorer or something. BUT! You have to hold right click to do it, not left click."/><Run Text=" there was a really annoying bug with left click that i couldn't solve after like 2 hours of debugging"/><Run Text="; it basically froze the entire program, requiring you to restart it."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The rich text editor doesn't work at all so just ignore it for now. Typical expected shortcuts (Ctrl + S to save)"/><Run Text=" work also. And finally, dont use the Open in New Window button. It's quite broken and closing the main window "/><Run Text="will"/><Run Text=" cause all other windows to close"/><Run Text=" due to a bug in visual studios 2017 apparently which is annoying "/></TextBlock>
